  "commentary": "With SPX at 6763.37 sitting right in the thick negative gamma zone between the max negative gamma at 6760 (-16.1B) and max positive gamma at 6780 (+7.1B), dealers are actively buying this dip after the recent wall break and GEX surge events. The breakout regime with -25.2B total GEX means dealers will continue amplifying moves - buying any further weakness toward 6760/6755 and selling strength if we push toward the 6780 positive gamma wall. Key levels to watch are 6760 downside (max buying pressure) and 6780 upside (selling pressure kicks in), with the current spot positioned for continued volatile, trending moves in either direction.\n\nBottom line: expect wild swings with dealers pushing price away from current levels toward either 6760 or 6780.",
